WestAir
Passenger Information
CHECK-IN TIME
Passengers requiring tickets should arrive 40 minutes before
scheduled departure time. All reservations are subject to
cancellation if passenger has not checked in 30 minutes
before scheduled departure time.
BAGGAGE
Luggage limitations are two pieces, total weight not to exceed
50 pounds. Any extra luggage may be subject to an additional
charge and will be carried on a space-available basis.
AIRCRAFT
WestAir utilizes twin engine jet-prop powered de Havilland
DASH-6 and Cessna 402 aircraft.
RESPONSIBILITY
WestAir reserves the right to cancel or change schedules or
fares and substitute appropriate equipment without notice.
Schedules shown are based on expected flying times and
departure and arrival times are not guaranteed. Passage may
be refused to any person when necessary to comply with
government regulations, tariff rules or for reasons beyond the
control of WestAir.
TICKET REFUND
Tickets purchased directly from WestAir may be mailed to
WestAir's executive offices. Tickets purchased fromt ravel
agencies must be refunded by the issuing party.
CONVENIENT FACILITIES
WestAir is now located in the United Airlines concourse of the
North Terminal building. Our ticket counter is next to Eastern
Airlines, and our boarding gate is gate #74. Our new
convenient gate location will enable you to make quick and
easy connections from WestAir to United with a connection
time as little as 30 minutes.
